## Database & Prisma Rules

### Schema Design
- Use `cuid()` for IDs instead of `autoincrement`
- Always include `createdAt` and `updatedAt` timestamps
- Use enums for fixed value sets
- Proper foreign key relationships

```prisma
// ‚úÖ Good
model Pomodoro {
  id        String   @id @default(cuid())
  title     String
  duration  Int
  userId    String
  createdAt DateTime @default(now())
  updatedAt DateTime @updatedAt
  user      User     @relation(fields: [userId], references: [id])
}

// ‚ùå Bad - no timestamps, no relations
model Pomodoro {
  id     Int     @id @default(autoincrement())
  title  String
  userId String
}
```

### Database Queries
- **Group related queries** in dedicated functions (don't scatter them)
- **Use Prisma's fluent API** with proper error handling
- **Include relations** when needed with `include` or `select`
- **Prefer Server Actions** over API routes for simple operations
- **Keep business logic** close to where it's used

```typescript
// ‚úÖ GOOD - Server Action with organized database logic
'use server';

export async function createPomodoro(formData: FormData) {
  const session = await getSession();

  const data = {
    title: formData.get('title'),
    duration: parseInt(formData.get('duration')),
    userId: session.user.id,
  };

  // Zod validation
  const validatedData = createPomodoroSchema.parse(data);

  // Database operation
  const pomodoro = await prisma.pomodoro.create({
    data: validatedData,
    include: { user: { select: { name: true } } }
  });

  revalidatePath('/dashboard');
  return pomodoro;
}

// ‚úÖ GOOD - API Route for complex operations
export async function GET(request: Request) {
  const { searchParams } = new URL(request.url);
  const userId = searchParams.get('userId');

  if (!userId) {
    return NextResponse.json({ error: 'User ID required' }, { status: 400 });
  }

  const pomodoros = await prisma.pomodoro.findMany({
    where: { userId },
    orderBy: { createdAt: 'desc' },
    take: 10,
    select: {
      id: true,
      title: true,
      duration: true,
      createdAt: true,
    }
  });

  return NextResponse.json(pomodoros);
}
```

